messages.message:
Hi team,

How do you set the correct log_level so that we can see all the logs  (info, debug, error) in crafting sandbox?
I’m trying to see the following log, but I didn’t find any info logs:
https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/0ed3db4a/webserver/api-server/src/py/instabase/api_server_apps/handler/api/v2/aihub_build.py#L1307

I changed logging.info (http://logging.info)(...) to logging.error(...), and then I was able to see the error logs in api-server logs.

I also tried setting log_level in env-local-overrides.json, but it didn’t work:
```{
  "base": {
    "log_level": "DEBUG"
  },
  "docker-local": {
    "log_level": "DEBUG"
  }
}```
cc : @ayesha.ali
